### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health/
//Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Auth - Login (JWT)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/token/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}


{
  "username": "userf",
  "password": "123123"
}

### Auth - Refresh (JWT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/token/refresh/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refresh": "{{login.response.body.refresh}}"
}

### Me - Get Profile
# @name getMe
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me/
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access}}

### Part Request Status - List
# @name listPartStatuses
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/part-request-statuses/
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.access}}

### Me - Update Profile
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/me/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "city": "Riyadh"
}

### Users - Create
# @name createUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{accept}}

{
  "email": "user3@example.com",
  "username": "usera",
  "name": "User Three",
  "phone": "+15551234569",
  "city": "Riyadh",
  "role": "user",
  "rating": null,
  "password": "123123"
}

### Users - List
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Spare Parts - Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spare-parts/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Brake Pad2",
  "description": "Front brake pad2 set",
  "price": "199.99"
}

### Spare Parts - List
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/spare-parts/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Part Request Status - Create
# @name createPartStatus
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/part-request-statuses/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "code": "open",
  "label": "Open",
  "is_terminal": false
}

### Part Request - Create
# @name createPartRequest
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/part-requests/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "requester": {{userId}},
  "title": "Need Toyota Corolla 2018 front bumper",
  "description": "Original part preferred, used is fine.",
  "status": {{partStatusId}},
  "city": "Riyadh"
}

### Part Request - Create With Two Images (multipart)
# Run "Auth - Login" first, then copy the new access token into @accessToken.
# Run "Me - Get Profile" and copy the returned numeric "id" into @userId.
# Run "Part Request Status - List" and copy a real status id into @partStatusId.
# Raw multipart bodies are more reliable with manual variables than chained response placeholders.
# This request is the clean backend-only upload test for request images.
# @name createPartRequestWithTwoImages
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/part-requests/
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: {{accept}}

--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="requester"

{{userId}}
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

HTTP multipart image upload check
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

This request should create the part request and save two image rows plus two files in media/part_requests.
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="status"

{{partStatusId}}
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="city"

Cairo
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="images"; filename="sample_part_1.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./fixtures/sample_part.jpg
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="images"; filename="sample_part_2.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./fixtures/sample_part.jpg
--AutoSpareRequestBoundary--

### Part Image - Add (multipart, raw boundary)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/part-images/
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="part_request"

{{partRequestId}}
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="sample_part.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./fixtures/sample_part.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

