### Message Status - Add (manual IDs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/message-statuses/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "message": {{messageId}},
  "user": {{userId}},
  "status": "sent"
}

### Mobile Device - Send Test Request Notification
# Use a real authenticated user's access token and a device that belongs to that user.
# If mobile_device_id or request_id is omitted, the backend will try the latest available match.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mobile-devices/test-request-notification/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "mobile_device_id": 9,
  "request_id": 18,
  "request_title": "Push notification test",
  "request_description": "This is a backend-triggered test request notification.",
  "seller_name": "Backend Test"
}
